The paper deals with Multi-Armed Bandit problems, which are a common topic in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses regret bounds, which are related to game theory and decision making, making cs.GT (Game Theory) a likely category as well. The Bandits with Knapsacks theory involves resource consumption, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions dynamic pricing and online bidding, which are common topics in cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
